\mathcal F(e^{-|x|} +|x|e^{-|x|})
\displaystyle\mathcal F(e^{-|x|})={1\over \pi (1+w^2)}
2 \Re{\left [ \int_0^{\infty} dx \, x \, e^{-(1-i w)x}\right ]} = 2 \Re{\left [ \frac1{(1-i w)^2}\right]} = 2\frac{1-w^2}{(1+w^2)^2 }
-\sqrt{2/\pi}
F[|x|e^{-|x|}] = F[|x|]\ast F[e^{-|x|}] = \frac{1}{\xi^2}\ast \frac{1}{1+\xi^2} = -\frac{\xi^2-1}{(1+\xi^2)^2}.
